binclock - a simple binary clock

Written Wed 23 May 2012 by Ian D Brunton < iandbrunton at gmail dot com >

Outputs current %H:%M:%S as a binary string.

Options:
	-0	The character to represent the 0 bit.

	-1	The character to represent the 1 bit.

	-s	The character to separate hours, minutes, and seconds.
